rows.name: Woolsey Hall
rows.accessibility: Accessible entrance with automatic door opener in front rotunda on Grove Street side. There is access into Woolsey Hall concert area during a performance from a ramp located at the main entrance rotunda facing Grove Street. Otherwise this door is normally kept locked. For wheelchair seating or other accommodations, please call the sponsor of the event. A unisex accessible bathroom is located on the middle tier off the rotunda near the men's room and closest to Grove Street. It can be reached by exiting the main doors of Woolsey Hall. Persons using wheelchairs and attending functions in the Presidents' Reception room and upper-level meeting areas are requested to call (203) 432-0455 or 432-2325 in advance.
